narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Significantly developed my formal modeling skills and knowledge of political competition. This course helped me to think critically about existing models of political competition and their strengths and weaknesses.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I very much enjoyed the format and pacing of the course. The content was rigorous and at times quite challenging, but for good reason (i.e. it wasn't difficult just to be difficult). I didn't think there were any particular weaknesses. Perhaps half a lecture or so on Kuhn-Tucker could be cut so that a bit more of the Kantian material can be covered in the future.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: If they are interested in formal modeling and/or political competition, absolutely.
